The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 A passenger died on board an Indian flight after suffering a severe cardiac arrest on Sunday afternoon. S.K. Udaypuria, a resident of Bhubaneswar, was travelling from Bangkok to Calcutta on his way home on flight IC 732. He suffered the cardiac arrest mid-air. The plane landed at Calcutta airport at 3.40 pm and he was immediately attended to by an Airports Authority of India doctor, who pronounced him dead. The body has been sent for post-mortem.

