 Six persons were arrested at Dakshindari, in Lake Town, on Saturday night for allegedly assembling with the intention of looting a jewellery shop in the area. According to police, the cops patrolling the area became suspicious about the movement of the men and chased them. They were carrying four swords, a single-shot firearm and four rounds of cartridges. 

 Two 

 people were arrested on Sunday afternoon for allegedly assaulting 

 an employee of a company on AJC Bose Road. Ramesh Bajoria, 

 the employee, said in his complaint that he came to Calcutta 

 from Mumbai to settle the dues of the other employees of the 

 company, which has been closed for the past 10 years. ?I was 

 in my office when two people ? the owner of the plot on which 

 the company?s factory is located and his son ? came in. They 

 pinned me to the ground and beat me up,? Bajoria alleged. 

 He lodged the complaint at Beniapukur police station. 

 Gajendra Karnani, the owner of the plot, and his son Asish 

 were later arrested. 

 A 30-year-old man was arrested in Thakurpukur on Sunday on the charges of raping a 21-year-old woman. The complaint was lodged by the victim. She told police that Kartik Shit, a distant relative, entered the room in which she was sleeping alone and raped her. Shit was arrested soon after in the house. The woman has been sent for medical examination.

