 The 19th annual state conference of Indian Psychiatric Society, West Bengal branch, was held at Advanced Neuro Psychiatric Institute, Joka, on Sunday. Kedar Ranjan Banerjee was re-elected secretary of the society and A.N. Chowdhury was elected the new president. 

 The Calcutta Municipal Corporation authorities have decided to conduct anti-mosquito drives in educational institutions in the civic area for a fee. Chief municipal health officer Deb Dwaipayan Chattopadhyay said the institutions will be able to afford the fee.

